<paragraph blockId="27.[211,1445,727,955]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">
REMARQUE. — Les exemplaires capturés au mont Nimba par M. Lamotte et R. Roy ont été décrits par 
<bibRefCitation author="JOSEPH K. J." box="[1249,1393,727,750]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" pagination="29 - 36" refId="ref41792" refString="JOSEPH K. J. 1959. - On a collection of fig insects (Chalcidoidea: Agaonidae) from French Guinea. Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London (B) 28: 29 - 36." type="journal article" year="1959">Joseph (1959)</bibRefCitation>
sous le nom de 
<emphasis box="[323,473,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joseph" authorityYear="1959" box="[323,469,762,785]" class="Insecta" family="Agaonidae" genus="Agaon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatum">A. tridentatum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Dans un premier temps, cette espèce a été considérée comme un synonyme de 
<taxonomicName authority="Dalman (Wiebes 1968)" authorityName="Dalman (Wiebes" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Agaonidae" genus="Agaon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradoxum">
<emphasis box="[1304,1443,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">A. paradoxum</emphasis>
Dalman (
<bibRefCitation author="WIEBES J. T." box="[306,446,796,819]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" pagination="346 - 355" refId="ref44799" refString="WIEBES J. T. 1968. - Species of Agaon from Congo (Kinshasa), with notes on synonymy (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea). Proceedings of the Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen (C) 71: 346 - 355." type="journal article" year="1968">Wiebes 1968</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, puis comme un synonyme de 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterston" authorityName="Waterston" authorityYear="1914" box="[780,1015,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Agaonidae" genus="Agaon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatum">
<emphasis box="[780,901,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">A. fasciatum</emphasis>
Waterston
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BERG C. C. &amp; WIEBES J. T." box="[1030,1249,796,819]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" refId="ref39991" refString="BERG C. C. &amp; WIEBES J. T. 1992. - African fig trees and fig wasps. Verhandelingen der Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen, Amsterdam, 298 p." type="book" year="1992">Berg &amp; Wiebes 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="WIEBES J. T." box="[1270,1410,796,819]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" pagination="395 - 407" refId="ref44976" refString="WIEBES J. T. 1989. - Agaonidae (Hymenoptera Chalcidoidea) and Ficus (Moraceae): fig wasp and their figs, V. (Agaon). Proceedings of the Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen (C) 92: 395 - 407." type="journal article" year="1989">Wiebes 1989</bibRefCitation>
). Il semble que le 
<typeStatus box="[353,400,830,853]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
, introuvable au MNHN Paris, n’ait jamais été examiné par Wiebes (
<bibRefCitation author="WIEBES J. T." box="[1073,1209,830,853]" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" pagination="346 - 355" refId="ref44799" refString="WIEBES J. T. 1968. - Species of Agaon from Congo (Kinshasa), with notes on synonymy (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea). Proceedings of the Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen (C) 71: 346 - 355." type="journal article" year="1968">Wiebes 1968</bibRefCitation>
) et que par conséquent un doute majeur subsiste sur la validité de cette espèce. S’il s’agissait d’un synonyme de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dalman (Wiebes" authorityYear="1968" box="[1081,1217,864,887]" class="Insecta" family="Agaonidae" genus="Agaon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradoxum">
<emphasis box="[1081,1217,864,887]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">A. paradoxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, l’hôte serait 
<emphasis box="[1348,1445,864,887]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">
<taxonomicName box="[1348,1441,864,887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barteri">F. barteri</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Dans les deux cas, ces espèces de figuiers n’ont pas encore été recensées dans la région du mont Nimba, bien qu’elles existent dans les régions voisines (
<collectingCountry box="[564,702,932,955]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[713,846,932,955]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="27" pageNumber="134">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
